title: Slow Cooker Cheesy Jalapeño Veggie
directions: Place veggies and chopped jalapeño in the bottom of your slow cooker, then season with onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture, then top with cubed cream cheese.
Cover slow cooker and cook on high for 2 hours (or on low for 4).
Stir everything together until melted and smooth and serve hot.
ingredients: 1 (8 oz.) package sharp cheddar cheese, grated
